NAME
       sysmon - real-time CPU, memory, and process monitor

SYNOPSIS
       sysmon

DESCRIPTION
       Interactive monitor for the running Cervus system. Displays a
       header with uptime and process count, a CPU and a memory bar with
       coloured thresholds (green < 50% < yellow < 80% < red), and a
       sortable table of every task currently known to the scheduler.

       The screen is refreshed on a configurable interval (default 1 s).
       Input is read in non-blocking raw mode through the
       TIOCSNONBLOCK ioctl.

KEYS
       q, Ctrl-C    quit
       p            pause / resume refresh
       s            cycle the sort key (cpu / runtime / pid / name)
       c, r, i, n   set sort key directly
       arrows       move selection
       PageUp/Down  scroll selection by 10
       k            send a kill signal to the selected process
                    (confirms first; do not pick init)
       + / -        speed up / slow down refresh by 100 ms
       ?, h         toggle the help line

DISPLAY COLUMNS
       PID     process id
       PPID    parent pid
       UID     owner
       STATE   RUN, RDY, BLK or ZMB
       PRIO    scheduler priority
       CPU%    fraction of one CPU consumed in the last refresh interval
       RUNTIME total user-mode time since exec
       NAME    process name as reported by the kernel

SEE ALSO
       ps(1), meminfo(1), cpuinfo(1)
